cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper presents a real-time object-based SLAM system that leverages object recognition algorithms. This falls under the domain of computer vision.
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper presents a SLAM system that can be used in robotics applications, as it provides accurate mapping of the environment.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The object recognition algorithm used in the paper is based on bags of binary words, which is a machine learning technique.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents an AI-based system that can recognize and map objects in real-time.
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper presents a system that combines computer vision and object recognition techniques to achieve real-time object-based SLAM.
